Until now, electricity was mainly sourced from hydropower, natural gas, and coal (Dapice, 2018). As these resources are considered exploited and finite, the rising electricity load is met with imports and a stronger focus on coal mining. The Vietnamese government has set its energy targets oriented toward RET, specifically hydro, wind, and solar energy by committing to reduce GHG emissions by 25 % until 2030 at the 21st\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
